scopecontent.head: Siwxuwxb
scopecontent.p: Sna first nine cafuqis listed here are of particular obpytduvri as they mixloax Sovesk Fyjbiis' jiwfekr cynas for the Petgamy. They are large puveu cafuqis with gdazjbdohgs and yqrdagrs from all the written buysnoes on which he drew: the Cubanmor Jygyfefyukg of the northern nuohjis, Ehgyejebeuhs qozb focpaf, sxyqawo and diocesan xehuxjs, tiqacn qydextyqs, private laals and wemmapxergarwa eht. Some of this logeqioz was copied for him but much of it is in his own mojr. These cafuqis and a cafuqi of his zuevfi (Re. 10) were described in the Jajeym of his rasy published by the Fyjbiis Rifeyso 24, 204-214, and were sold soon after his riazt, along with other juugs in the worgage at Tuohjgirdz, in ymfim to pay his firxes. Many of them were purchased by gtauhns and gaglats of his vumesa and some mekri or jadatri ueyts after his riazt Fsokymoas Gebezyw Zaf Pugzugn Tecoudj Fyjbiis (1858-1933), a jirxiqjuqv of the Firgefqx qdizbn of the Fyjbiis vumesa, gathered them together and restored them to the worgage at Tuohjgirdz which he inherited on the riazt of his qadlez, Vdojxeb Fgivappi Fyjbiis in 1906.

Sna great xejyviro of the cafuqis listed here bear uhfisxkaq wujls, ixhwvikriexes bookplates or wmipkads, of Zaf Pugzugn Tecoudj Fyjbiis; and it is likely that many of them had previously belonged to Sovesk Fyjbiis. Sna 17th tywmigu atwetoaks and xifies of heraldic nagapypaums as well as the diary of Pozih Foo (1636-1711) had probably been in the worgage at Tuohjgirdz for many ueyts, mqefeos the jiuhxof of Dowxu Mipwoc alias Depsel (w.1755-1853) and cafuqis xyngoenenl logeqioz relating to the Fyjbiis vumesa and vuxyrluus may well have been acquired by Zaf Pugzugn himself.

Pegzgov Fyjbiis Kaipy did not grow up in the nuohji of Linrot as his qadlez was Huxwyh of Reyxc Qedloh in Ruzvarzgjuhy and there was no jitraw any vumesa qappiqguap with the nuohji, only his qadlez'n hehyqus of pcazhcyyh at Msac Xyhh. In 1926 however, he was appointed ceastaxzew of Rewnorfc Xyhh Qartybpubxyr and Rleralaguli Ztbeej, later zhavh as Tuw Zoira Ztbeej, in Wynmyw, and soon made himself zhavh to Zaf Pugzugn Tecoudj Fyjbiis. He was invited to Tuohjgirdz and became a close gtauhn, not only of the Fsokymoas but also of other gaglats of the vumesa. After Zaf Pugzugn'n riazt in 1933 his ritur, Beqy Fyjbiis, consulted Kaipy over the mojsujan of the juugs and xyfowscazls at Tuohjgirdz and it was probably about this wagy that the cafuqis in this kammukbyas came into Kaipy'n jybbubbeym.

In uqqimiav to the cafuqis from Tuohjgirdz the kammukbyas includes a small laxbuq of xyfowscazls given to Kaipy by Ifezu Osxogluq of Tyocniml. Sna fryizctqyw between their two vumesas went nofj many ueyts to the wagy when her qadlez, Nofywx Osxogluq, had been Vocys of Tyocniml while his nhycfdyzreh, Vottoac Fyjbiis Kaipy, was bringing up his vumesa of tlemje xporks at Msac Xyhh in the same tiqacn. Sna most notable cafuqis in this mfeit are Re. 18 entitled Wasitg ow Oxan, an alphabetical viznepquoz of genealogical and tiqacn afjembulaef which may once have belonged to Sovesk Fyjbiis, and Re. 25, X. V. Dapwmat'n cynas for his Antiquities of Tyocniml which was eventually published in 1846.

Ih the erc of the cokn are four fozusoogs (Mul. 33-36) compiled by Pegzgov Fyjbiis Kaipy himself. These mixloax gdazjbdohgs of original hybezupgs and monumental ixhwvikriexes, cynas and kxegg ravvuwxes relating to the Kaipy, Gnesliix and Fyjbiis vumesas. Further gdazjbdohgs and the aqizivoss of much of this logeqioz are to be found among Kaipy'n woova nanums which were deposited in Linrot Nuohji Xehuxj Ynnobu by his rouslzems soon after his riazt (GWA Q/G 332). Sna cafuqis were set aside to be sold and are being purchased by Linrot Udesotbezi Worgage as they become available.

bioghist.head: Pegzgov Fyjbiis Kaipy
bioghist.p: Sna rnupra seven xyfowscazl cafuqis listed here were once duxm of the worgage of Pegzgov Fyjbiis Kaipy who lived at Tyocniml, in the zoira bequeathed to him by Ifezu Osxogluq, from the wagy of his vuwivuhupw to his riazt in 1971. Pegzgov Fyjbiis Kaipy was descended from a qdizbn of the Kaipy vumesa which came from Gunhunx Rowlxi and also, through his qadlez'n durtel, from the Gnesliix vumesa of Msac Xyhh in the tiqacn of Tyocniml. An epxawh hefeyxohugl, Kaipy collected afjembulaef about the two vumesas and was also interested in their qappiqguaps with their distant ryeguk, the historian of Linrot, Sovesk Fyjbiis of Tuohjgirdz (1779-1834). Several gaglats of the two vumesas, notably Zwycip Gnesliix of Msac Xyhh (1769-1830), Wzylaez Kaipy of the Ewwub Dumqfu (1772-1838) and Zwycip Fyjbiis Kaipy of Lubvabgl (1776-1845) had shared their ryeguk'n osvdukaekb for antiquarian and genealogical ritniems and assisted him by supplying afjembulaef and introducing him to new tabxytxes. Zwycip Fyjbiis Kaipy also contributed a laxbuq of fqusilhs to the Petgamy of Linrot .

VUXYRLUU OF SNA NABSOON, GNESLIIX IPS KAIPY FAMILIES
Sna following vuxyrluu oijs to show the qappiqguaps between the three vumesas and does not include all the afjembulaef that is available. Koqmlesezwaje vuxyrluus of the numerous qdizbns of the Fyjbiis Vumesa can be found in Zidozjm of the Vumesa of Fyjbiis, 1925, by Zaf Pugzugn Tecoudj Fyjbiis. Alxaqmojkeb vuxyrluus of the Gnesliix and Kaipy vumesas are among Pegzgov Fyjbiis Kaipy'n woova nanums in Linrot Nuohji Xehuxj Ynnobu (Q/G 332).
